Ahead of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) primary scheduled for May 28, the party will on Wednesday holds its 96th National Executive Committee (NEC) Meeting. The party, it was learnt, will at the meeting decides its modus operandi on how to go about the process of next elections. The party NEC will also take decision on the report submitted by the zoning committee led by the governor of Benue state, Samuel Ortom. Recall that the issue of zoning has been the bone of contention in the party and while the South and Northern zones of the PDP have been laying claim to produce the next presidential candidate, the party leadership had kept mute. Also recall that shortly after the PDP lost the 2019 election, the party had set up a committee led by the Bauchi state governor, Bala Mohammed to look into why the party failed. One of the recommendation of the committee was that the 2023 presidential ticket should be thrown open. Toeing this line, the zoning committee led by Ortom, it was gathered that one of its recommendations was that the presidential ticket should be thrown open. POLL However, the PDP National Secretary, Sen. Samuel Anyanwu, in a statement on Saturday announced that the party will hold its NEC on Wednesday. The statement reads: “All members of the National Executive Committee of our great Party are invited to the 96th NEC meeting.” The party enjoined all members to attend the meeting.